+## FL-40 authoritative staging evaluation
+
+The protected GitHub `staging` environment must define `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`,
+`HEYDOC_MEDGEMMA_ENDPOINT` and `HEYDOC_MEDGEMMA_KEY`. The workflow explicitly
+maps them; attaching an environment does not itself create arbitrary process
+environment variables. Required-reviewer protection must remain enabled. Never
+print or pass these values on the command line.
+
+The authoritative job uses
+`verification/data/eval-manifests/authoritative-v1.json` — all 707 attested
+conforming cases at the pinned corpus snapshot. `--limit` and `--cases` are for
+non-certifying connectivity/calibration runs only and are refused with a live
+`--gate`. Before generation the CLI requires every requested adapter to be
+mechanically live-enabled and credentialed. Each report turn records adapter
+mode/model/prompt hash; any mock turn, replay judge or absent clinician sign-off
+invalidates a live report. No partial fixture/report set is written if either
+backend fails validation.
+
+Do not dispatch until MedGemma reachability and the protected environment have
+been independently verified. This workflow remains synthetic-only and does not
+open patient eligibility.
+
