+## FL-40: authoritative-run provenance + certification-manifest hardening (2026-07-21)
+
+P2.1 reconciliation found a safety-critical false-certification path in the new
+staging eval: `--mode live` described the fixture recorder, but did not prove the
+Claude/MedGemma adapters actually entered their live paths; the workflow comment
+said staging secrets were injected but did not explicitly reference them; and
+the default `--limit 45` selected the first sorted directories — all CARD cases.
+
+**Resolved fail-closed.** The manual staging job now explicitly maps the protected
+Claude key and MedGemma endpoint/key, sets `HEYDOC_MEDGEMMA_LIVE=1`, and runs only
+against `verification/data/eval-manifests/authoritative-v1.json`. The manifest
+pins all 707 attested conforming cases with a count and SHA-256 over the ordered
+IDs; tamper, duplicate, missing or malformed case IDs refuse. A live `--gate`
+run cannot use `--limit` or `--cases` in place of a certification manifest.
+
+**Provenance is now contract data.** Every EvalRunReport turn carries the Step-4
+adapter `mode`, model and prompt hash. The zod/JSON contract rejects a live report
+if any turn says mock, the communication judge is not live, or clinician sign-off
+is absent. The CLI preflights every requested backend before generation. Fixture
+and report writes are run-atomic: invalid or incomplete two-backend evidence is
+not persisted.
+
+`test/contract-eval-live-preflight.js` proves missing manifest, missing Claude
+credentials, missing MedGemma live configuration, manifest tamper and workflow
+wiring all fail closed; `contract-eval-report` proves mock provenance cannot enter
+a live-labelled report. Added to `npm test`. This does not run the evaluation or
+move patient eligibility; authoritative fixtures and MedGemma connectivity remain
+operator/infra-gated.
+
+---
